-- day-two.cell: Experiment 4 вЂ” Multi-day continuity
-- Citizens live Day 2 informed by Day 1 outcomes.
-- Tests: chaining programs, using prior results as inputs, temporal coherence
-- Prerequisite: Run millhaven-5.cell first, collect results into day-one-results

вЉў city
  yield description в‰Ў "Millhaven is a small coastal town of about 5,000 people. Harbor district, main street, residential hill, lighthouse on the point. Wednesday in early March. Yesterday's drizzle has cleared to cold sunshine."
  yield day в‰Ў "Wednesday, March 5"
  yield yesterday в‰Ў "Tuesday, March 4"

-- Day 1 summaries (data cells вЂ” would be populated from prior run)
вЉў day-one-rosa
  yield name в‰Ў "Rosa Delgado"
  yield age в‰Ў 52
  yield occupation в‰Ў "head librarian"
  yield yesterday-summary в‰Ў "Opened library early, dealt with leaking east window. Mrs. Patel returned a mystery. Children's reading group read Island of the Blue Dolphins. Helped Marco Reyes with lighthouse project. Ate chowder at Carla's. Worried about Thursday's budget meeting."

вЉў day-one-tom
  yield name в‰Ў "Tom Harwick"
  yield age в‰Ў 38
  yield occupation в‰Ў "commercial fisherman"
  yield yesterday-summary в‰Ў "Light haul of Dungeness crab. Sold to Pelletier's. Ran into Dale Hutchins who may be selling his boat. Returned a library book. Engine maintenance on the Ellie Mae. Worried about thin crab season and whether to cut Danny's hours."

вЉў day-one-maya
  yield name в‰Ў "Maya Chen"
  yield age в‰Ў 17
  yield occupation в‰Ў "high school junior"
  yield yesterday-summary в‰Ў "AP History class, ate lunch alone in the library. Walked to Anchor Bakery for sourdough. Sketched the lighthouse from the overlook bench. Texted Destiny about English essay. Thinking about college applications and whether leaving Millhaven is brave or restless. Jaden smiled at her in the hallway."

-- Day 2 citizens вЂ” they remember yesterday
вЉў rosa-day2
  given cityв†’description
  given cityв†’day
  given day-one-rosaв†’name
  given day-one-rosaв†’age
  given day-one-rosaв†’occupation
  given day-one-rosaв†’yesterday-summary
  yield morning
  yield afternoon
  yield evening
  yield thoughts
  yield what-changed
  в€ґ You are В«nameВ», age В«ageВ», the В«occupationВ» of Millhaven Public Library.
    Town: В«descriptionВ». Today is В«dayВ».

    YESTERDAY: В«yesterday-summaryВ»

    Live today. What do you do in the morning, afternoon, evening?
    What has changed since yesterday? What carries forward?
    Share your private thoughts.

    Be specific. Reference yesterday's events where they naturally connect.
  вЉЁ morning is a string
  вЉЁ what-changed is a string

